text:
Generally old school kopitiam coffee can be trusted, and old stalls like these really gives you the no-frills, no nonsense quality coffee and tea that really makes you feel like got a loving uncle or auntie giving you the reassuring look with an approving smile and nod everytime you take a sip.

Teh is well balanced and not watered down which unfortunately is quite common nowadays but not here
One of the better coffee in round market.
Great coffee at Tampines Round Market! It costs $1.20 for a cup of nice coffee at the food centre. The aunty made such aromatic coffee.
Their hot coffee with milk is very strong and well balanced.

Coffee is sour and diluted, the guy likely the son probably reuses the powder many times to cut costs. The lady aunty smokes regularly behind the stall after her smoke she collects dirty cups does not wash her hands and picks up new cups when people order, quite unhygienic.
